result.execSummary:
The defendant Desmond D. Gonzalez was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Invade Privacy - Enter Private Property [Modifiers: Repeater], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 942.08(2)(d).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Concurrent with: Any existing sentence being served.

superMiscConds.notes: Costs to be paid directly to the Waushara County Clerk of Court within 60 days or establish a payment plan.  Failure to pay may result in suspension of your driver's license, tax intercept, a civil judgment being entered against you, a warrant being issued for your arrest for contempt and/or the debt being turned over to a collection agency.

Defendant to undergo a Psychological Evaluation and comply with any further counseling and/or treatment as deemed appropriate by the supervising agent, which may include Sex Offender Treatment, which would be solely at the agent's discretion.

The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician.  No contact with both victims A.C.L. (16CM-38) and K.E.S. (15CM-463).
No DNA sample ordered as Defendant previously provided the same through another conviction.  Mandatory DNA Surcharge ordered by the Court.

Signature Bond ordered w/conditions.  Court releases FPT and JT and places the case in a suspended status.  Status conference scheduled for October 26, 2016 at 01:45 pm.
